package = com.ditchoom.boringssl.canonical

# Bindings-FREE owner def. No `headers` and no wrappers → cinterop produces a klib with an EMPTY
# binding surface. `libraryPaths` + `staticLibraries` (+ the linux pthread/dl floor) are injected by
# the generateCanonicalDef task (see build.gradle.kts) so the ONE canonical BoringSSL archive rides
# into the published cinterop klib's `included/` (embedArchive=true semantics — RFC §2: "ship the
# ingredients, not the bindings"). A co-linking consumer that adds its OWN external (headers-only)
# cinterops resolves every crypto/ssl symbol against this single embedded copy.

---
